con:interface.name: SimplyConnect API
con:interface.con:description:
Simply Connect API for third-party apps

Terms of Service

In order to access the SimplyConnect API you must have written consent from Simply Connect HIE. Any other use of this API is prohibited. Please contact us.

con:method.name: loginUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This step is not mandatory, but recommended. Once per session, prior to calling other endpoints make a call to `POST /auth/login` OR `POST /auth/validateToken`. Successful response from any of these endpoints indicates that:

  1. SimplyHIE REST service is up & running

  2. Supplied token is valid

Login

con:parameter.con:name: timeZoneOffset
con:parameter.con:description: Timezone Offset - the time difference between UTC time and local time, in minutes (example -120 for GMT+2; overwrites the value specified during registration; affects events filtering by date in `GET /events`)

con:method.name: validateTokenUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This step is not mandatory, but recommended. Once per session, prior to calling other endpoints make a call to `POST /auth/login` OR `POST /auth/validateToken`. Successful response from any of these endpoints indicates that:

  1. SimplyHIE REST service is up & running

  2. Supplied token is valid

Validate token

con:method.name: completeRegistrationUsingPOST
con:method.con:description: Call this method once to get access token when your registration application is approved. After the registration is completed send your access token in `X-Auth-Token` header with any request that requires authentication. Step 2 (final). Complete the registration and generate access token

con:parameter.con:name: flowId
con:parameter.con:description: registration flow guid (returned in response to `POST /register/signup/application`)

con:parameter.con:name: appName
con:parameter.con:description: application name (the same as was specified in request to `POST /register/signup/application`)

con:method.name: registerApplicationUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This method creates a new API User account with non-active status (active = false) and account type of APPLICATION.
All applications are reviewed by Administration (SimplyHIE dev team). Contact us if you want to speed up the review process.
The registered user (if approved) will have access to Simply Connect external API.
Before the registration is completed it may be resubmitted with a different data. Step 1. Register new application (Sign Up as Third-Party application)

con:parameter.con:name: timeZoneOffset
con:parameter.con:description: Timezone Offset - the time difference between UTC time and local time, in minutes (example -120 for GMT+2; affects events filtering by date in `GET /events`)

con:method.name: registerNucleusUserUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This method creates a new (mobile?) User account with associated non-active Contact and account type of PROVIDER.
No confirmation required for the user and (s)he immediately gets access to Simply Connect mobile API. The autocreated contact will be activated after completion of the regular registration in Web S.C.

Required privileges

SPECIAL_NUCLEUS
Register new Nucleus device user (User registration initiated by Third-Party App)
